# Weather app using React.js, Typescript and Styled Components![](data:image/jpeg;base64, )

> NOTE: Typescript is used in a way so that it's easy for beginners as well. Any operations that requires complex typescript types are ignored and `any` type is used that means any kind of type is accepted


### Step 1: Getting started and setting up
1. Node and npm/yarn are assumed to be installed.
2. Download or Clone this [template](https://github.com/coderrahul/weather-template) repo where the basic dependencies, icons, backgrounds are already added.
3. Do `npm install` or `yarn` from the root folder of the project to install the required dependencies.
